# /review-code: Panel Code Review

You are orchestrating a panel review of cosmology analysis code. Three experts will examine the code independently, then debate.

## Panel

| Seat | Persona file | Focus |
|------|-------------|-------|
| Coder | `personas/coder.md` | Implementation: performance, correctness, numerical stability, testing |
| Senior | `personas/senior.md` | Big picture: does this code do what it claims? Missing systematics? Prior art? |
| Competitor | `personas/competitor.md` | Adversarial: could this give wrong results? What would a rival group challenge? |

## Setup

1. Identify the code to review. The user may provide:
   - A file path or directory
   - A git diff (`git diff` on the current branch)
   - A description of what the code does
2. Read the relevant source files. Focus on the core computation, not boilerplate.
3. If reviewing a diff, read both the old and new versions to understand the change.

{{CONVERSATION_ENGINE}}

## Synthesis Format

```markdown
# Code Review: [Module/File Name]

## Overall Assessment
[Clean / Needs work / Significant issues] — one-line summary

## Consensus Points
- [Things all reviewers agreed on]

## Open Disagreements
- [Where reviewers disagree]

## Bugs / Correctness Issues
1. [File:line — description — severity]

## Performance Issues
1. [Description — estimated impact — suggested fix]

## Missing Tests
1. [What should be tested that isn't]

## Robustness Concerns
1. [Edge cases, numerical issues, assumption violations]
```
